cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper introduces a new extension of lambda calculus for parallel programming, which falls under the scope of programming languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses Curry-Howard correspondence to extract the parallel lambda calculus from logics intermediate between classical and intuitionistic logic. This falls under the scope of logic in computer science. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on parallel programming and communication patterns between parallel processes, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper showcases examples of parallel programs, including algorithms on graphs, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper uses graph-based communication as a key feature of the parallel lambda calculus, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics.
